## 2. System Architecture

### 2.1 Architecture Overview

The system follows a layered architecture within the VS Code extension:

![Architecture Diagram](data:image/png;base64...)

Architecture Diagram

**Layers:** 1. **Presentation Layer** — VS Code UI (notifications, quick picks, output channels, status bar) 2. **Command Layer** — extension.ts registers commands and orchestrates workflows 3. **Business Logic Layer** — injector.ts (update strategies), checksum.ts (integrity logic) 4. **Data Access Layer** — Direct filesystem I/O via Node.js fs module 5. **External Tools** — Git CLI (for gen-checksums), PowerShell (for sync)

### 2.2 Component Diagram

![Component Diagram](data:image/png;base64...)

Component Diagram

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Component | Responsibility | Technology |
| extension.ts | Command registration, UX orchestration, status bar | VS Code API |
| checksum.ts | Hash computation, manifest load/save, status detection | Node.js crypto |
| injector.ts | File injection, safe update, backup, filtered copy | Node.js fs |
| config.ts | Component definitions, paths, labels | TypeScript constants |
| indexer.ts | Code intelligence indexer execution | Child process |
| gen-checksums.js | CI manifest generation from git | Node.js + git CLI |
| sync-from-source.ps1 | Cross-repo file sync | PowerShell |

### 2.3 Deployment Architecture

The extension is packaged as a VSIX and distributed via: - VS Code Marketplace (vsce publish) - Open VSX Registry (ovsx publish)

**Runtime deployment:** - Extension runs inside VS Code Extension Host process - No separate server or container needed - All data stored in workspace filesystem

### 2.4 Communication Patterns

|  |  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| From | To | Protocol | Pattern | Description |
| extension.ts | checksum.ts | Function call | Sync | Direct module import |
| extension.ts | injector.ts | Function call | Async | Async for UI interactions |
| gen-checksums.js | Git CLI | Child process | Sync | execSync for git commands |
| sync-from-source.ps1 | Filesystem | PowerShell cmdlets | Sync | Get-FileHash, Copy-Item |
| GitHub Actions | npm scripts | Shell | Sync | Sequential CI steps |

## 3. Module Design

Note: This extension has no REST APIs. This section covers the internal module interfaces.

### 3.1 Module: checksum.ts

**Exports:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Function | Signature | Description |
| computeFileHash | (filePath: string) => string | SHA-256 hex digest of file |
| loadBundledManifest | (extensionPath: string) => ChecksumManifest \| null | Load from resources/ |
| loadWorkspaceManifest | (workspaceRoot: string) => WorkspaceManifest \| null | Load from .kiro/ |
| saveWorkspaceManifest | (workspaceRoot: string, manifest: WorkspaceManifest) => void | Save to .kiro/ |
| recordFileInjected | (manifest, relativePath, version, hash) => void | Record injection |
| getFileStatuses | (workspaceRoot, extensionPath) => FileStatus[] | Compute all statuses |
| detectModifiedFiles | (workspaceRoot, extensionPath) => ModifiedFile[] | Find hash mismatches |
| isUpgradeAvailable | (workspaceRoot, extensionPath) => boolean | Any file newer? |
| migrateLegacyVersion | (workspaceRoot, extensionPath) => void | Migrate .sdlc-version |
| buildManifestAfterInject | (workspaceRoot, extensionPath) => void | Rebuild manifest |

**Interfaces:**

interface ChecksumManifest {
 version: string;
 generatedAt: string;
 files: Record<string, FileChecksum>;
}

interface FileChecksum {
 hash: string; // SHA-256 hex (64 chars)
 version: string; // semver
 injectedAt: string; // ISO 8601
}

interface WorkspaceManifest {
 lastUpdated: string;
 files: Record<string, WorkspaceFileEntry>;
}

interface WorkspaceFileEntry {
 version: string;
 hash: string;
 injectedAt: string;
}

interface FileStatus {
 relativePath: string;
 workspaceVersion: string;
 bundledVersion: string;
 state: "current" | "outdated" | "modified" | "missing";
}

interface ModifiedFile {
 relativePath: string;
 expectedHash: string;
 actualHash: string;
 injectedVersion: string;
}

### 3.2 Module: injector.ts

**Exports:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Function | Signature | Description |
| injectAll | (root, extensionPath) => Promise<string[]> | Inject all components |
| injectSelective | (root, extensionPath) => Promise<string[]> | User picks components |
| safeUpdate | (root, extensionPath) => Promise<string[]> | Update with safety |
| checkStatus | (workspaceRoot) => Record<string, boolean> | Component existence |
| getVersionReport | (root, extensionPath) => string | Detailed version report |

**Update Strategies:**

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Strategy | Function | Behavior |
| Force Update | forceUpdate() | Overwrite all files, rebuild manifest |
| Skip Modified | updateSkipModified() | Skip files in ModifiedFile set |
| Backup & Overwrite | updateWithBackup() | Copy to .kiro/.sdlc-backup/{timestamp}/, then force |

### 3.3 Module: gen-checksums.js

**Algorithm:** 1. Read package.json → extract version 2. git ls-tree -r --name-only HEAD -- {RESOURCE\_PATHS} → file list 3. For each file: git show HEAD:{path} → SHA-256 4. Write JSON manifest to resources/.sdlc-checksums.json

**Tracked Paths (RESOURCE\_PATHS):** - .kiro/agents/ - .kiro/hooks/ - .kiro/steering/ - documents/templates/ - .analysis/code-intelligence/index-config.json

### 3.4 Module: sync-from-source.ps1

**Parameters:** - -DryRun (switch) — preview mode

**Configuration (hardcoded):** - SOURCE\_ROOT: C:\projects\kotlin\MCPOrchestration - DEST\_ROOT: C:\projects\kiro\FEC\_CR\_Builder - MAPPINGS: 3 source→dest pairs - SKIP\_DIRS: settings, node\_modules, **pycache**, out, dist, .git - SKIP\_FILES: mcp.json, mcp.json,bk

**Algorithm:**

for each mapping:
 enumerate source files recursively
 for each file:
 if path matches skip pattern → skip
 if not exists in dest → copy (NEW)
 else if MD5(src) != MD5(dest) → overwrite (CHANGED)
 else → skip (unchanged)
print summary

## 4. Data Storage Design

### 4.1 File Locations

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| File | Location | Created By | Read By |
| Bundled Manifest | {extensionPath}/resources/.sdlc-checksums.json | gen-checksums.js (CI) | checksum.ts |
| Workspace Manifest | {workspaceRoot}/.kiro/.sdlc-manifest.json | injector.ts | checksum.ts |
| Legacy Version | {workspaceRoot}/.kiro/.sdlc-version | (deprecated) | checksum.ts (migration) |
| Backup Files | {workspaceRoot}/.kiro/.sdlc-backup/{timestamp}/ | injector.ts | User (manual recovery) |

### 4.2 JSON Schemas

**Bundled Manifest Schema:**

{
 "version": "1.0.5",
 "generatedAt": "2026-05-10T04:22:47.128Z",
 "files": {
 ".kiro/agents/ba-agent.md": {
 "hash": "4b35262c5de6e127b6b4dd6f1ff2d42fec3b6c819d341b9f1207580fea22d3e4",
 "version": "1.0.5",
 "injectedAt": "2026-05-10T04:22:47.128Z"
 }
 }
}

**Workspace Manifest Schema:**

{
 "lastUpdated": "2026-05-10T04:30:00.000Z",
 "files": {
 ".kiro/agents/ba-agent.md": {
 "version": "1.0.5",
 "hash": "4b35262c5de6e127b6b4dd6f1ff2d42fec3b6c819d341b9f1207580fea22d3e4",
 "injectedAt": "2026-05-10T04:30:00.000Z"
 }
 }
}

## 5. CI/CD Pipeline Design

### 5.1 CI Workflow (ci.yml)

**Trigger:** Push to main OR PR targeting main, with paths: kiro-sdlc-agents/\*\*

**Steps:**

jobs:
 build:
 runs-on: ubuntu-latest
 defaults:
 run:
 working-directory: kiro-sdlc-agents
 steps:
 - actions/checkout@v4
 - actions/setup-node@v4 (node 20)
 - npm ci
 - npm run copy-resources
 - npm run gen-checksums
 - npm run compile
 - npx vsce package --no-dependencies
 - verify \*.vsix exists

### 5.2 Publish Workflow (publish.yml)

**Trigger:** Tag v\* OR manual dispatch (target: both/vscode-only/openvsx-only)

**Jobs:** 1. build — same as CI + upload VSIX artifact 2. publish-vscode — download artifact → npx vsce publish --packagePath \*.vsix -p $VSCE\_PAT 3. publish-openvsx — download artifact → npx ovsx publish \*.vsix -p $OVSX\_TOKEN

**Conditional execution:** - publish-vscode: runs if tag push OR target=both OR target=vscode-only - publish-openvsx: runs if tag push OR target=both OR target=openvsx-only

### 5.3 Key Design Decisions

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Decision | Rationale |
| Workflows at repo root | GitHub requires .github/workflows/ at repo root |
| working-directory directive | Extension code is in subdirectory |
| paths filter | Avoid triggering on non-extension changes |
| --no-dependencies flag | Extension has no runtime npm dependencies |
| Separate build + publish jobs | Build once, publish to multiple targets |
| Artifact upload between jobs | Ensures same VSIX is published everywhere |

## 6. Security Design

### 6.1 Secrets Management

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Secret | Storage | Usage | Rotation |
| VSCE\_PAT | GitHub Secrets | VS Code Marketplace publish | Per PAT expiry |
| OVSX\_TOKEN | GitHub Secrets | Open VSX publish | Per token expiry |

### 6.2 Integrity Guarantees

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Guarantee | Mechanism |
| Bundled manifest tamper-proof | Stored inside VSIX (signed package) |
| Hash reproducibility | gen-checksums reads git HEAD, not filesystem |
| No secret exposure | GitHub Actions masks secrets in logs |

### 6.3 Input Validation

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Input | Validation | Location |
| Manifest JSON | try/catch on JSON.parse, return null on failure | checksum.ts |
| File paths | path.join (prevents traversal), existsSync check | checksum.ts, injector.ts |
| Git output | trim + split, filter empty lines | gen-checksums.js |

## 7. Error Handling Design

### 7.1 Error Recovery Matrix

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Error | Component | Recovery | User Impact |
| Bundled manifest missing | checksum.ts | Return null/empty | Checksum features disabled |
| Workspace manifest corrupted | checksum.ts | Return null, rebuild on next inject | Temporary loss of modification detection |
| File read permission denied | checksum.ts | Skip file, continue | File shows as “missing” |
| Injection source not found | injector.ts | Show warning, skip component | Component not injected |
| Injection copy fails | injector.ts | Show error, continue with others | Partial injection |
| Git not available | gen-checksums.js | Script exits with error | CI build fails (expected) |
| Source repo not found | sync-from-source.ps1 | Print “SKIP”, continue | Mapping skipped |

### 7.2 Logging Strategy

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Event | Level | Output |
| Manifest loaded | (silent) | — |
| Upgrade available | Info | VS Code notification |
| Migration completed | (silent) | — |
| Injection success | Info | VS Code notification |
| Injection failure | Error | VS Code error message |
| gen-checksums success | Console | stdout (CI logs) |
| gen-checksums skip file | Warn | console.warn |
| Sync new/changed | Console | colored stdout |

## 8. Performance Considerations

### 8.1 Activation Performance

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Operation | Expected Time | Optimization |
| Load bundled manifest (JSON parse) | < 5ms | Single file read |
| Load workspace manifest (JSON parse) | < 5ms | Single file read |
| Compute hashes for 50 files | < 400ms | Synchronous, sequential |
| Total activation overhead | < 500ms | No async I/O needed |

### 8.2 gen-checksums Performance

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Operation | Expected Time | Notes |
| git ls-tree | < 100ms | Single git command |
| git show × 50 files | < 3s | Sequential, could parallelize |
| JSON write | < 10ms | Single file |
| Total | < 5s | Acceptable for CI |

## 9. Implementation Checklist

### Files to Create/Modify

|  |  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| # | File | Action | Description |
| 1 | src/checksum.ts | CREATE | Checksum management module |
| 2 | src/injector.ts | MODIFY | Add safe update logic, backup strategy |
| 3 | src/extension.ts | MODIFY | Add update command, upgrade check on activation |
| 4 | src/config.ts | MODIFY | Add component definitions if needed |
| 5 | scripts/gen-checksums.js | CREATE | CI manifest generation script |
| 6 | scripts/sync-from-source.ps1 | CREATE | Cross-repo sync script (repo root) |
| 7 | .github/workflows/ci.yml | CREATE | CI workflow at repo root |
| 8 | .github/workflows/publish.yml | CREATE | Publish workflow at repo root |
| 9 | package.json | MODIFY | Add gen-checksums to prepublish, bump version |
| 10 | resources/.sdlc-checksums.json | GENERATED | Output of gen-checksums |

### Implementation Order

1. src/checksum.ts — core hashing and manifest logic (no dependencies)
2. src/injector.ts — update strategies using checksum module
3. src/extension.ts — wire up commands and activation check
4. scripts/gen-checksums.js — CI script
5. package.json — add scripts, bump version
6. .github/workflows/ — CI and publish workflows
7. scripts/sync-from-source.ps1 — sync tooling (independent)
8. Test: run gen-checksums locally, verify manifest
9. Test: install extension, verify activation check works

